title: [Alhan'aht River, Coastal Gap]
description: Reflecting the moonlight with their pale color, spectacularly tall sandstone cliffs cause the rainforest to come to an abrupt dead-end, blocking out any further growth, save for the vines that climb up the cliffs and hang down with invitation to climb up.  The rushing river hurtles straight out through a single wide gap in the cliff, quickly disappearing out of sight.
location: the environs of the Saewehna Lagoon
